<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223933" src="https://i2.wp.com/tooxclusive.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/davido-ring.png?resize=476%2C500&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="476" height="500" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The contributions to the Private Sector Coalition Against COVID-19 (CACOVID) set up by the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) to raise funds to combat Coronavirus hit the total of 19.488 billion naira. The likes of Aliko Dangote, Jim Ovia , Femi Otedola, Segun Agbaje, and other banks have all contributed. Davido’s father, Adedeji Adeleke also donated the sum of 750 million naira to the Osun state government to help those affected financially by the disease. Davido has reacted to the new list with a message on Instagram. The “Risky” singer hopes that the government would make sure to use the funds to good use. He wrote:  “to everyone else that contributed !! Now let’s make sure the government puts these funds to good use !!” See the photo below:   ?? to everyone else that contributed !! Now let’s make sure the government puts these funds to good use !!! A post shared by  Davido Adeleke (@davidoofficial) on Apr 5, 2020 at 4:42am PDT //www.instagram.com/embed.js The post Davido Reacts As Donations Made By Private Companies To Fight COVID-19 Hits 19.488 Billion Naira appeared first on tooXclusive. Source: Too Xclusive First name * Email * Phone Number  Check your inbox or spam folder to confirm your subscription.  Nigerian Singer, Davido has reacted to the large donations that have been made to curb the spread of coronavirus in Nigeria, asking the government to put the funds to good use. On Friday, contributions to the Private Sector Coalition Against COVID-19 (CACOVID) set up by the Central Bank of Nigeria… April 5, 2020 In "Entertainment" The Coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic is real in Nigeria with nearly 100 confirmed cases recorded so far in the country. But government, banks and private sector leaders are taking steps to curb the spread of the virus and reduc